'''为工作和自由向华盛顿进军'''，也称“向华盛顿的伟大进军”<ref>{{Cite journal|quote = Yet by the end of the year the company was promoting its Great March to Washington album, featuring `I Have A Dream' in its entirety.|title = Recording the Dream|first = Brian|last = Ward|work = [[History_Today|History Today]]|date = April 1998|url = http://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst?docId=5001329940|journal = |access-date = 2012-01-09|archive-date = 2011-06-28|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110628214628/http://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst?docId=5001329940|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|publisher = [[Washington_Post|Washington Post]]|url = http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/24/AR2010082405003.html?hpid=opinionsbox1|title = Still striving for MLK's dream in the 21st century|first = Martin Luther|last = King III|date = August 25, 2010|accessdate = 2012-01-09|archive-date = 2016-12-13|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161213233102/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/08/24/AR2010082405003.html?hpid=opinionsbox1|dead-url = no}}</ref>，发生于1963年8月28日，是美国历史上最大的一场人权政治集会<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?flash=true&doc=96 |title=我们的档案，美国档案馆 |accessdate=2012-01-09 |archive-date=2018-07-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706142119/https://www.ourdocuments.gov/doc.php?flash=true |dead-url=no }}</ref>，目的在于争取[[非裔美国人|非裔美国人]]的[[民权|民权]]和经济权利。集会中，[[马丁·路德·金|马丁·路德·金]]在[[林肯纪念堂|林肯纪念堂]]前发表了旨在推动族际和谐的著名演讲“[[我有一个梦想|我有一个梦想]]”<ref name="scholastic">{{Cite news| title = The Sixties | publisher = ''Junior Scholastic''  o| date = 1994-02-11   | url = | pages = 5–6   | accessdate = 2008-12-01 }}</ref>。

游行由众多民权、工权和宗教社团<ref name="Veterans">{{Cite web |title=March on Washington for Jobs & Freedom |url=http://www.crmvet.org/tim/tim63b.htm#1963mow |publisher=Veterans of the Civil Rights Movement |accessdate=2012-01-09 |archive-date=2016-08-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816034441/http://www.crmvet.org/tim/tim63b.htm#1963mow |dead-url=no }}</ref>在“工作与自由”的主题下组织<ref name="scholastic"/>，估计参与者人数达到20万（警方）至30万（组织者）之间。观察者估计75%至80%的参与者为黑人，其他的则属于白人和其他族群。

这次行动为推动[[1964年民權法案|1964年民權法案]]和[[1965年投票权法案|1965年投票权法案]]的通过做出了巨大贡献。

此事件在影片《[[阿甘正传|阿甘正传]]》即有体现。

